Heat oil in 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until well browned on both sides. Remove chicken from skillet. Stir soup, water, paprika and black pepper in skillet. Heat to a boil. Stir rice and broccoli in skillet. Reduce heat to low. Return chicken to skillet. Sprinkle additional paprika and black pepper over chicken. Cover and cook 5 minutes. or until chicken is cooked through and rice is tender.